                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/530: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-01T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1927—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 1—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>315. Following from American consul at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 31, 4 p.m. <hi rend="italic">Shasi</hi> sailed this morning for
                            Shanghai with 12 Americans including 4 women. <hi rend="italic"
                                >Tungwo</hi> will sail tomorrow morning with approximately 40
                            Americans. Foreign banks and newspapers still closed and business
                            practically at a standstill with no immediate prospects of
                            improvements.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
